result.execSummary:
The defendant Buffalo Taylor Nelis was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor [Modifiers: Habitual Criminality], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes:
If def is placed on probation or extended supervision & owes financial obligations ordered by the Court at the time of discharge, a civil judgment may be entered against the def for all unpaid financial obligations.
  While on supervision the Def is to pay their financial obligations thru the Clerk of Court, which may include payments on restitution, fines, costs, surcharges, etc that are court ordered.
The payments are to be paid directly to the Clerk of Court Office at:
Ashland Co Clerk of Circuit Court
201 Main Street West - Room 307
Ashland, WI  54806

miscConds.notes: Defendant is placed on a payment plan of $25 a month beginning 60 days from today.
To seek, obtain and maintain full time employment/full time schooling or a combination of the two.

Def is to undergo counseling for criminal thinking through a Cognitive-Thinking for Change therapy program.
  The Def is to obtain counseling as directed by DOC at the expense of the Def.

Defendant shall not possess/consume alcoholic beverages, illegal drugs, drug paraphernalia or any mind altering substances (MAS).  MAS means alcoholic beverages, controlled substances other than those prescribed by treating physician to the Def & taken only as prescribed, inhalants, synthetic marijuana or a similar substance, and/or over-the-counter medications used contrary to label instructions.  THE DEFENDANT IS TO MAINTAIN ABSOLUTE SOBRIETY.
The Defendant shall not enter any bars, taverns, liquor stores (any place where the primary purpose is the sale of alcohol) where mind altering substances are present, consumed or sold..
  Not to associate with any known drug users or those involved in trafficking, other than in a professional group counseling setting or meeting.
  The Def is to provide a DNA specimen @ the ACJ.
  The Def is subject to random UA testing.
Enroll in, actively participate, comply with all rules and conditions of and successfully complete the Ashland County Drug Court Program. The Parties specifically agree that successful completion of Drug court is an integral part of the plea agreement. Should the Defendant fail to successfully complete drug court, the parties agree that there would be both a violation of the specific terms of the original sentence and as such, if discharged from the Ashland County Drug Court Program, the case will return to court for re-sentencing. If the defendant is not compliant with terms or  conditions of the Ashland County Drug Court programs, and portion of the imposed and stayed conditional jail in 16CF181, Count 1 may be used for violations/sanctions or other terms of this agreement that are violated.
Undergo alcohol/drug assessment and complete recommended treatment-responsible for finding the funding for any treatment/counseling recommended.

judgments.action: Guilty Due to No Contest Plea

supervisions.notes:
Def granted work/huber release priv.
Def granted good time credit.
Def granted credit for time served.
Consecutive to: any other sentence

All remaining financial obligations are reduced to a civil judgment.  Within 30 days of def's release from custody he is to submit a financial disclosure statement to the Court & to begin paying $20/mo on the 1st of the month after the release date.
